%I A065401 #28 May 11 2026 19:37:12
%S A065401 1,4,22,1474
%N A065401 Number of normal play partisan games born on or before day n.
%C A065401 Fraser and Wolfe prove upper and lower bounds on a(n+1) in terms of a(n). In particular they give the (probably quite weak) lower bound of 3*10^12 and the upper bound of 10^434 for a(4). - _Christopher E. Thompson_, Aug 06 2015
%C A065401 Koki Suetsugu improved the lower and upper bounds of a(4), and the lower bound is 10^28.2, and the upper bound is 4*10^184. - _Zhujun Zhang_, May 06 2026
%D A065401 Dan Calistrate, Marc Paulhus and David Wolfe, On the lattice structure of finite games, in More Games of No Chance (Berkeley, CA, 2000), Math. Sci. Res. Inst. Publ., 42, Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge, 2002, pp. 25-30.
%D A065401 J. H. Conway, On Numbers and Games, Academic Press, NY, 1976.
%D A065401 Aaron N. Siegel, Combinatorial Game Theory, AMS Graduate Texts in Mathematics Vol 146 (2013), p. 158.
%H A065401 William E. Fraser and David Wolfe, <a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.tcs.2003.05.001">Counting the number of games</a>, Theoret. Comput. Sci. 313 (2004), pp. 527-532.
%H A065401 Koki Suetsugu, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2208.13403">Improving upper and lower bounds of the number of games born by day 4</a>, arXiv:2208.13403 [math.CO], 2022-2024; pp. 447-460 in Games of No Chance 6, edited by U. Larsson, Math. Sci. Res. Inst. Publ. 71, Cambridge Univ. Press, 2025.
%F A065401 a(n) = A125990(2*A114561(n)). - _Antti Karttunen_, Oct 18 2018
%Y A065401 Cf. A065402, A065407, A047995, A037142, A114561, A125990, A126011.
%K A065401 nonn,hard,more,changed
%O A065401 0,2
%A A065401 _R. K. Guy_, Nov 23 2001
%E A065401 _Dean Hickerson_ and Robert Li found a(3) in 1974.
